SIMPLE: lull
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lull
<hw>Lull</hw> <pr>(l⟦ucr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Lulled</conjf> <pr>(l⟦ucr⟧ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Lulling</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to OD.
<ets>lullen</ets> to sing to sleep, G. <ets>lullen</ets>, Dan.
<ets>lulle</ets>, Sw. <ets>lulla</ets>; all of imitative origin. Cf.
<er>Loll</er>, <er>Lollard</er>.]</ety> <def>To cause to rest by
soothing influences; to compose; to calm; to soothe; to quiet.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧ To <xex>lull</xex> him soft asleep.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such sweet compulsion doth in music lie,⟦br⟧
To <qex>lull</qex> the daughters of necessity.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lull</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lull
<hw>Lull</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become gradually calm; to
subside; to cease or abate for a time; <as>as, the storm
<ex>lulls</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lull</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Lull
<hw>Lull</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The power or quality of
soothing; that which soothes; a lullaby.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Young.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A temporary cessation of storm or
confusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lullaby</ent>⟦br⟧
